		<div id="comment_body_64775901"><p>I think it matters a lot. This is really basic competency stuff and they want to be in charge of security, and use a direct kernel interface? Even if Microsoft <em>did</em> provide a reasonable API for doing what they are doing, odds are good that if they screwed up badly enough with it they could still cause severe problems with the system up to and including abnormal termination. I am happy to throw Microsoft under the same bus, but they still have to go down.</p></div>
	</div>

